By default log files of Sar command is located at /var/log/sysstat/saXX( date) file, where the dd parameter indicates the current day.\par
Using sar you can monitor performance of various Linux subsystems (CPU, Memory, I/O..) in real time.\par
Using sar, you can also collect all performance data on an on-going basis, store them, and do historical analysis to identify bottlenecks.\par
$ sar 1 3              \tab\tab      <= system CPU statistics 3 times (with 1 second interval).\par
$ strings  /var/log/sysstat/sa20   <= strings read binary to human readable \par
