Q:14 What is Network Bonding ?\par
Network bonding is the aggregation of multiple Lan cards into a single bonded interface to provide fault tolerance and high performance. Network bonding is also known as NIC Teaming.\par
\par
Q:15 What  are the different modes of Network bonding in Linux ?\par
Below are list of modes used in Network Bonding :\par
balance-rr or 0 \endash  round-robin mode for fault tolerance and load balancing.\par
active-backup or 1 \endash  Sets active-backup mode for fault tolerance.\par
balance-xor or 2 \endash  Sets an XOR (exclusive-or) mode for fault tolerance and load balancing.\par
broadcast or 3 \endash  Sets a broadcast mode for fault tolerance. All transmissions are sent on all slave interfaces.\par
802.3ad or 4  \endash  Sets an IEEE 802.3ad dynamic link aggregation mode. Creates aggregation groups that share the same speed & duplex settings.\par
balance-tlb or 5 \endash   Sets a Transmit Load Balancing (TLB) mode for fault tolerance & load balancing.\par
balance-alb or 6 \endash   Sets an Active Load Balancing (ALB) mode for fault tolerance & load balancing.\par
\par
